1
00:00:24,787 --> 00:00:31,411
Hello, everyone, and welcome to Method Happenings, a show for and about the city of Method.

2
00:00:32,312 --> 00:00:51,085
And I am John Petrella, and the purpose of this program is to give Method citizens facts and information to help you make informed choices and to discover city services or businesses you may not have been aware of.

3
00:00:52,680 --> 00:01:05,431
And today's show is about the Lions International, which was founded in 1917, and is universally recognized for fighting preventable blindness.

4
00:01:05,451 --> 00:01:07,192
It's a great organization.

5
00:01:07,612 --> 00:01:14,998
And our guest today is Sharon Diaso, who is an active member of the local chapter.

6
00:01:15,519 --> 00:01:17,180
Welcome to Method Happenings.

7
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:19,022
Thank you for joining us, Sharon.

8
00:01:19,522 --> 00:01:25,906
Thank you, John and kind staff, for including me in your program today in the Lions Club.

9
00:01:26,466 --> 00:01:33,030
This year, I am vice president, and I think I am incoming president for the September 2026 year.

10
00:01:33,290 --> 00:01:33,710
Thank you.

11
00:01:33,991 --> 00:01:34,571
Very nice.

12
00:01:34,831 --> 00:01:35,912
All right.

13
00:01:36,272 --> 00:01:37,513
We start the show off.

14
00:01:38,644 --> 00:01:42,629
Same way every episode, just tell us a little bit about yourself.

15
00:01:42,669 --> 00:01:43,731
Who's Sharon D'Oso?

16
00:01:43,931 --> 00:01:55,245
Okay, I was born in Malden to John D'Eso of Everett and Camilla Torino D'Eso of Naples, Italy, and I've been a resident of the city since I was four.

17
00:01:55,846 --> 00:02:00,448
I won't tell you how many years that's been now because I don't want to get on that subject today.

18
00:02:00,468 --> 00:02:03,229
John, I attended Medford Public Schools.

19
00:02:04,630 --> 00:02:06,130
I joined clubs.

20
00:02:07,131 --> 00:02:09,592
I was very active in traveling.

21
00:02:10,192 --> 00:02:13,413
I became a student at UMass Boston.

22
00:02:13,453 --> 00:02:14,754
I'm a UMass Boston girl.

23
00:02:15,254 --> 00:02:18,775
I received my bachelor's degree in English.

24
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:24,758
I received my master's degree from Suffolk University, trying to keep schools in Boston.

25
00:02:25,398 --> 00:02:29,422
and postgraduate from Northeastern and British Literature.

26
00:02:29,442 --> 00:02:36,027
I do remember great days in this building because I taught for five to seven years at the high school.

27
00:02:36,748 --> 00:02:42,012
I worked for 20 years before that with the stock market as a trading assistant.

28
00:02:42,553 --> 00:02:49,618
And now I'm just finishing my 11th to 12th year at Bunker Hill and helping a principal in this fine city.

29
00:02:50,219 --> 00:02:50,899
Very nice.

30
00:02:51,660 --> 00:02:52,541
That's nice to know.

31
00:02:54,122 --> 00:03:01,413
All right, so next question naturally is, you know, talk about the Lions International.

32
00:03:01,954 --> 00:03:04,217
Who are they and what do they do?

33
00:03:05,777 --> 00:03:17,341
I have to explain some misconceptions because a lot of people say, well, I'm looking up LCIF, or I'm looking up Medford Lions.

34
00:03:18,121 --> 00:03:19,021
What is the difference?

35
00:03:19,601 --> 00:03:26,624
So I thought today I would define LCIF, will you, and the member clubs.

36
00:03:27,904 --> 00:03:31,988
LCIF is for the Lions Club International Foundation.

37
00:03:33,149 --> 00:03:40,535
That term encompasses every Nook and Cranny club internationally around the world.

38
00:03:41,256 --> 00:03:44,158
That is the legal charter name for our fund.

39
00:03:44,999 --> 00:03:47,901
So Medford Lions is a chapter of LCIF.

40
00:03:50,204 --> 00:04:06,421
LCI is the same thing, and I can tell you a little bit about the 109 fine years, and in a simple sentence, let you know that people like yourselves who were very fond of businesses,

41
00:04:07,302 --> 00:04:11,305
established small businesses in Chicago in 1917.

42
00:04:11,825 --> 00:04:13,587
They were very successful, John.

43
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:19,991
And a group of these businessmen, not being sexist at the time, of course, it just happened that way.

44
00:04:20,411 --> 00:04:27,777
And they wanted to get a cause going, not only for their community, but could they be going for USA?

45
00:04:28,557 --> 00:04:29,518
So they did.

46
00:04:29,998 --> 00:04:36,282
At their next meeting, they said, what is important to us and what does the world see as important?

47
00:04:36,882 --> 00:04:37,222
Eyesight.

48
00:04:38,043 --> 00:04:45,608
So their cause became eyesight, hearing, diabetes, and disaster aid.

49
00:04:46,168 --> 00:04:56,795
So if anyone looks up LCI or LCIF or find a club, Medford Lyons, you'll come across the same magnitude of great information.

50
00:04:58,553 --> 00:04:59,454
Very interesting.

51
00:04:59,654 --> 00:05:03,516
All right, so we understand all that.

52
00:05:04,177 --> 00:05:08,100
What are the, I mean, today, what are the core initiatives?

53
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:11,502
I mean, for the Lions chapter, what's the core?

54
00:05:11,542 --> 00:05:12,382
What is it that you're?

55
00:05:12,663 --> 00:05:16,445
Interesting, I was thinking about this yesterday and also explained to Paul.

56
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:21,369
There's a plethora of interests around the world.

57
00:05:22,089 --> 00:05:32,355
We have, just in the major cities of this country, 10,000 clubs or charters that have been given to local communities.

58
00:05:33,976 --> 00:05:38,258
Worldwide, there are 50,000 clubs internationally.

59
00:05:38,939 --> 00:05:45,442
So, each club would kind of gear itself to, if they had 38 members,

60
00:05:46,923 --> 00:05:52,888
they, of course, would be able to run more events locally and maybe including some nearby communities.

61
00:05:53,449 --> 00:06:07,441
The smaller the club, we find that if we do organize a couple of very popular events during the year, like Turkey Raffle that's very big for us in November, that became very popular.

62
00:06:08,782 --> 00:06:12,125
Monday night coming is our scholarship night that we just established.

63
00:06:12,885 --> 00:06:13,906
only five years ago.

64
00:06:13,926 --> 00:06:28,522
It's only granted to students who are either eye impaired, hearing impaired, John, or who have come across a very high physical handicap during high school, but still do good achievement and have high character.

65
00:06:29,062 --> 00:06:30,483
So every club is different.

66
00:06:31,203 --> 00:06:33,764
Another good example is Malden.

67
00:06:33,784 --> 00:06:38,886
A lot of people will tell me, oh, I know people in the Malden club.

68
00:06:39,146 --> 00:06:42,467
I see the McCappies once a year holding their cans with the logo.

69
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:44,508
That's called Pennies for Sight.

70
00:06:45,108 --> 00:06:53,011
Every penny in all those cans, and I have helped in the past, will go to Eyes for Sight at Mass Eye Research.

71
00:06:53,291 --> 00:06:55,872
We'll be on Mass Eye in a year, Mass Eye Research.

72
00:06:56,352 --> 00:06:59,554
So every club designates its own needs.

73
00:06:59,854 --> 00:07:02,996
Now, Belmont is a very largely enrolled club.

74
00:07:03,537 --> 00:07:10,661
They give close to $10,000 a year to BUI research and also a scholarship.

75
00:07:11,101 --> 00:07:16,705
So they're all on the same aim, but they're done different ways.

76
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:18,005
OK.

77
00:07:18,305 --> 00:07:18,546
Yeah.

78
00:07:18,586 --> 00:07:30,992
We mostly give to Mass Eye Research, Tufts Eye Research, BUI Research, Jocelyn Diabetes, and now Juvenile Diabetes in disaster aid in scholarships.

79
00:07:31,212 --> 00:07:32,073
Well, that's quite a bit.

80
00:07:32,253 --> 00:07:36,455
I mean, obviously, you do some fundraising, and it's all, it really is.

81
00:07:36,515 --> 00:07:37,775
It's all great causes.

82
00:07:37,956 --> 00:07:40,237
It's nice to have that.

83
00:07:40,297 --> 00:07:41,137
That's good to hear.

84
00:07:41,918 --> 00:07:45,720
I don't think a lot of people would even think that.

85
00:07:47,194 --> 00:07:49,437
It was a learning experience for me, Joe.

86
00:07:49,777 --> 00:07:51,619
Being here was a learning experience.

87
00:07:51,699 --> 00:07:56,805
I'm finding out all the nooks and crannies that you and your fine staff do for a fine public service.

88
00:07:58,106 --> 00:08:03,512
And I think what I've learned, too, is many things happen.

89
00:08:03,752 --> 00:08:07,336
I was coaxed into being a member about 10 years ago.

90
00:08:07,957 --> 00:08:13,261
Two people I worked with at a local realtor's office because I was teaching at the college, so I had a day free.

91
00:08:14,162 --> 00:08:20,668
And I knew these people at Wilson Cutler and Epstein Food Brokerage, and I helped out on Fridays.

92
00:08:21,148 --> 00:08:30,556
And a couple of local well-known brokers, I won't mention their names because I didn't tell them about today, kept saying to me, you know, you get around and you enjoy being with people.

93
00:08:30,636 --> 00:08:31,677
You should be a lion.

94
00:08:31,757 --> 00:08:32,057
I'm like,

95
00:08:32,655 --> 00:08:37,380
a commitment, or how am I going to party with my friends, or how am I going to correct essays?

96
00:08:37,861 --> 00:08:44,068
So after the second year, I decided to go to an event, and I learned so much.

97
00:08:44,708 --> 00:08:47,351
First off, when I went, it was a comedy night.

98
00:08:48,052 --> 00:08:56,318
And famous John McGillivray, who did move to Chelmsford, and then Hampton, and then has since passed away, was a dynamic member of Lions.

99
00:08:56,758 --> 00:08:57,979
He was so happy to see me.

100
00:08:58,099 --> 00:09:00,801
And I'm like, John, I didn't know you were in this club.

101
00:09:01,201 --> 00:09:01,902
He said, sure.

102
00:09:01,922 --> 00:09:04,684
I think there must have been 100 people there that night, John.

103
00:09:04,784 --> 00:09:06,105
I think I knew 20 of them.

104
00:09:06,565 --> 00:09:09,067
And I said, OK, how much are the dues?

105
00:09:10,107 --> 00:09:16,130
very reasonable Jews in Medford, I'm going to join, thinking I could sit back and do this and that.

106
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:17,390
We're not demanding.

107
00:09:17,991 --> 00:09:25,894
But I learned through the last three or four years the dynamism that goes around with international alliance.

108
00:09:26,514 --> 00:09:34,738
And I can let you know two or three headliners that almost brought tears to my eyes, if you will.

109
00:09:36,190 --> 00:09:40,912
In the 50s, a war veteran was meeting with his buddy, who was a lion.

110
00:09:41,773 --> 00:09:45,374
And he brought his grandchild with him, who was blind.

111
00:09:46,255 --> 00:09:53,958
And the lion said, gee, I didn't realize that you had a grandchild who was blind.

112
00:09:53,998 --> 00:09:58,740
He said, yes, he's been blind since after delivery, post-delivery.

113
00:09:59,321 --> 00:10:00,161
And he said, really?

114
00:10:00,281 --> 00:10:04,003
So we didn't have a lot of funding at that time and weren't well known.

115
00:10:04,683 --> 00:10:11,586
And shortly afterwards, another lion met with his friend, and his grandchild was blind.

116
00:10:11,646 --> 00:10:12,166
OK.

117
00:10:12,286 --> 00:10:14,887
And so he said, you know, I'm going to look into this.

118
00:10:15,307 --> 00:10:22,870
So he contacted doctors who were familiar with infant blindness.

119
00:10:23,730 --> 00:10:25,170
And they said, what's different?

120
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:28,512
Well, they realized over doing research that lions paid for.

121
00:10:28,532 --> 00:10:29,472
Right.

122
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:36,721
that four out of five of these blind babies during a period of about a decade were preemies.

123
00:10:37,521 --> 00:10:37,862
Wow.

124
00:10:38,062 --> 00:10:43,869
So what was going on from birth to incubator in environment in treatment?

125
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:49,235
The variable was the amount of oxygen being pumped into the incubator.

126
00:10:50,588 --> 00:10:51,089
They lured it.

127
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:57,997
There have been very, very, very few diseases now of that kind for infants.

128
00:10:59,379 --> 00:11:00,420
I think it's remarkable.

129
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,301
Yeah, of course it is.

130
00:11:01,461 --> 00:11:06,988
And I was, oh, wow, no, I really want to go to this club.

131
00:11:07,048 --> 00:11:07,869
That's what happens.

132
00:11:07,889 --> 00:11:08,910
I know a lot of people.

133
00:11:09,897 --> 00:11:12,159
They're hesitant to get involved with anything.

134
00:11:12,499 --> 00:11:12,760
Yes.

135
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:18,805
But then once they do, they end up, it's shocking how many old friends, people you know.

136
00:11:18,825 --> 00:11:19,826
That's right.

137
00:11:20,147 --> 00:11:22,068
And they now become good friends.

138
00:11:22,569 --> 00:11:26,933
And the thing is, you're accomplishing a lot of good while you're a member of the club.

139
00:11:26,953 --> 00:11:27,413
Exactly.

140
00:11:27,473 --> 00:11:29,275
It just makes you feel good.

141
00:11:29,335 --> 00:11:29,816
Yeah.

142
00:11:30,016 --> 00:11:31,137
And we have fun.

143
00:11:31,517 --> 00:11:32,698
Yeah, that's what it's all about.

144
00:11:32,778 --> 00:11:35,521
We really have fun along the journey.

145
00:11:36,122 --> 00:11:53,618
Coincidentally, since being in Medford now for a number of years, I had to make a phone call a couple of years ago because we learned that Lion's Research, again, paid for the research for the non-curable retinitis pigmentosus.

146
00:11:54,579 --> 00:11:57,362
and they still don't have a treatment for that.

147
00:11:58,063 --> 00:12:12,576
So someone said to me, you know, there's a man in New England, he may be from near the Medford area, who received funding to go to one of the first treatments with an insertion of a retinal chip.

148
00:12:13,537 --> 00:12:16,561
and the accommodation of fine-tuning lenses.

149
00:12:17,021 --> 00:12:19,865
Here's his number, etc.

150
00:12:20,686 --> 00:12:23,689
I said, you know, maybe we should have him as a guest speaker for local clubs.

151
00:12:24,290 --> 00:12:28,815
It doesn't have to be a fundraiser, but let's teach our fellow Lions and neighborhood clubs

152
00:12:29,856 --> 00:12:32,059
about this man, you know, would he come forward?

153
00:12:32,079 --> 00:12:33,560
Some people don't want to talk about it.

154
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:33,961
Right.

155
00:12:34,021 --> 00:12:37,725
So I called one night and I introduced myself and just that.

156
00:12:37,785 --> 00:12:42,269
And she, I, before we hung up, I said, you know, it'd be very interesting.

157
00:12:42,329 --> 00:12:43,971
Let's meet before the dinner.

158
00:12:44,011 --> 00:12:45,593
And I'm so glad you're coming with your wife.

159
00:12:46,153 --> 00:12:47,415
He said, oh, no problem.

160
00:12:47,796 --> 00:12:56,368
I said, well, naturally, and I don't mean this as kind of a pun, I will pick you up unless your wife wants to meet me.

161
00:12:56,388 --> 00:12:58,351
And he said, no, you can come to the house.

162
00:12:58,972 --> 00:13:00,014
He lived two blocks from me.

163
00:13:01,195 --> 00:13:02,796
So he's a wonderful man.

164
00:13:02,836 --> 00:13:04,257
He's very active in Medford.

165
00:13:05,238 --> 00:13:07,920
Anthony, he went around, we mentioned his name, Dratola.

166
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:13,123
He has benefited from not seeing fine details, but profiles.

167
00:13:13,223 --> 00:13:14,604
And he was a wonderful speaker.

168
00:13:14,744 --> 00:13:20,749
And we congratulate him for making that brave step in that big surgery.

169
00:13:20,909 --> 00:13:21,349
Very good.

170
00:13:21,409 --> 00:13:26,392
Now that we got people interested, how do they join the Lions?

171
00:13:27,033 --> 00:13:29,374
Can you give us an address, an email?

172
00:13:30,896 --> 00:13:32,297
that you can share with the audience.

173
00:13:32,557 --> 00:13:33,618
Okay.

174
00:13:34,859 --> 00:13:41,625
I always tell people, like I have it in students, you don't make a statement, you don't make a commitment, unless you know your facts.

175
00:13:42,886 --> 00:13:48,651
So if they go on to LCIF, all in caps,

176
00:13:49,372 --> 00:14:02,240
They will bring up one or two pages, even a menu bar, where they can learn about a club somewhere, they can learn about causes, they can learn about special events that have been done.

177
00:14:02,701 --> 00:14:05,923
We have even supported people who were running a wedding.

178
00:14:06,603 --> 00:14:08,685
very, very poor community in Uganda.

179
00:14:09,245 --> 00:14:11,867
So all that is on LCIF.

180
00:14:13,208 --> 00:14:23,755
If you want to go into www.lionsclub.org, you'll see a finer and smaller imprint of what's going on in different clubs.

181
00:14:24,236 --> 00:14:30,300
In contact information for maybe presidents of malls in Belmont or Auburn, we divide it into districts.

182
00:14:33,242 --> 00:14:47,074
Also, anyone who wants to can email me at sharondeso, all one word, s-h-a-r-o-n-d-e-y-e-s-o at yahoo.com.

183
00:14:47,655 --> 00:14:50,798
I'm not shy about giving out my cell phone because there's a lot of people

184
00:14:51,398 --> 00:15:00,865
whose computers break down, who are older, and they'd like to come to our events, 781-572-5130.

185
00:15:01,005 --> 00:15:08,611
We've also included seniors, John, in our big foster care night, which we just had in March.

186
00:15:08,671 --> 00:15:10,312
It was an outstanding success.

187
00:15:10,753 --> 00:15:16,097
We included 130 items to donate to Plummer House in Salem.

188
00:15:16,437 --> 00:15:18,399
They will be part of our turkey raffle.

189
00:15:19,099 --> 00:15:22,481
in the fall because we love the kids.

190
00:15:22,881 --> 00:15:24,141
Great.

191
00:15:24,822 --> 00:15:25,162
All right.

192
00:15:25,702 --> 00:15:29,444
So is the Method Lions Club, what are you currently planning?

193
00:15:29,904 --> 00:15:31,905
Any events coming up?

194
00:15:32,665 --> 00:15:33,786
Projects in the work?

195
00:15:33,906 --> 00:15:35,587
What's going on in the coming months?

196
00:15:35,727 --> 00:15:39,389
Well, we decided, and we're going to vote on this next meeting,

197
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:54,509
We should consolidate the turkey raffle, which is quite popular, and the foster care night, because my theme in the fall, in November, is giving thanks.

198
00:15:55,270 --> 00:15:58,172
To count our blessings, bless our eyesight,

199
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:02,276
and to consolidate the funding that evening.

200
00:16:02,896 --> 00:16:06,459
And of course, we'll put flyers again around the city.

201
00:16:06,479 --> 00:16:12,785
We're going to have a real membership collaboration effort this time to expose us.

202
00:16:13,105 --> 00:16:19,390
Because a lot of people still think the Lions is this real old club where you hold a can,

203
00:16:22,032 --> 00:16:24,994
see boxes that collect eyeglasses.

204
00:16:25,614 --> 00:16:33,438
Number one, answering your question, we still have a drop-off box in the former Brookline Beacon Bank now, right in Medford Square.

205
00:16:34,079 --> 00:16:39,902
If you turn right around when you come in in the lobby, you'll see an eyeglass drop-off box.

206
00:16:40,082 --> 00:16:44,764
There's also a very decorative bag in the main lobby of City Hall when you walk in.

207
00:16:45,365 --> 00:16:48,966
You can leave hearing devices there and also eyeglasses.

208
00:16:49,247 --> 00:16:50,928
We're no longer taking cases.

209
00:16:52,548 --> 00:16:52,728
OK.

210
00:16:52,928 --> 00:17:14,992
Sadly, in the US, even though these are processed and sterilized, these are given to foreign countries because the health department, and I'm going to write a letter also to Bobby Kennedy now, because up to this date, they can't reuse, reprocess anything near the eyes in Massachusetts ophthalmologist offices.

211
00:17:15,332 --> 00:17:17,312
But they all are good used.

212
00:17:17,612 --> 00:17:17,852
Right.

213
00:17:17,892 --> 00:17:18,413
Believe me.

214
00:17:18,613 --> 00:17:18,833
Yeah.

215
00:17:19,473 --> 00:17:19,973
I hear you.

216
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:20,353
Yeah.

217
00:17:20,933 --> 00:17:22,134
strange some of the rules.

218
00:17:22,694 --> 00:17:24,795
Yes, yes, we'll get through it.

219
00:17:24,835 --> 00:17:26,516
Yes, I know you will.

220
00:17:28,337 --> 00:17:33,060
All right, one of the programs I know a little bit about, not much, is the Leo program.

221
00:17:34,581 --> 00:17:39,384
You know, and that's all about how the Lions support local kids.

222
00:17:39,844 --> 00:17:41,006
Correct.

223
00:17:41,446 --> 00:17:42,367
We're a small club.

224
00:17:42,568 --> 00:17:44,470
We did have 13 members.

225
00:17:44,871 --> 00:17:45,071
